## MODULE 1: PRODUCT POSITIONING AUDIT (300 words max)

**Answer these specific questions:**

1. **Core Value Proposition Test:** Complete this sentence from the PROJECT's perspective: "Unlike [competitor], [product] is the only platform that [unique mechanism]." If you can't complete it clearly, that's the #1 problem.

2. **User Focus Test:** Does the product try to serve too many user types? List each distinct user persona and assess if the product serves any of them DEEPLY vs all of them SHALLOWLY.

3. **Feature Coherence Test:** Do all features serve ONE unified narrative, or is it a "feature buffet"? Rank every major feature by how strongly it supports the core value proposition (1-10).

**Comparison Matrix (fill for this specific project):**

| Dimension | This Product | Duolingo | Coursera | LeetCode | ChatGPT |
|-----------|-------------|----------|---------|---------|---------|
| Learning model | [?] | Spaced repetition + gamified | Video + assignments | Problem sets + contests | Conversational |
| Engagement hooks | [?] | Streaks, XP, leaderboard | Certificates | Rankings, badges | None (utility) |
| Personalization | [?] | Adaptive difficulty | Course recommendations | Difficulty progression | Full conversation |
| Data flywheel | [?] | User data → better curriculum | Completion data | Submission data | Conversation data |
| Monetization | [?] | Freemium + ads | Subscriptions | Premium + enterprise | Subscriptions |

